The **Composer Human Task** exposes the Composer application in the Workplace 2 interface, allowing to open and edit document templates in the task editor. One or more document templates will be opened in a HTML5 view of Composer. The output of this task is an IPD file and (optionally) an XML file with Insertion Point states.

> Composer

Composer is a separate component of the Doxee Platform&reg;. Please refer to its [product documentation](/doxee-platform/docs/composer) for more information about its features and functionalities.

## Interface
![](data:image/png;base64,)Composer Human Task in the task editor of Workplace 2

## Configuration
The configuration of a Human Task is done in Process Designer. It consists of three mappings:

- **General parameters:** General properties of the Human Task

- **Input parameters:** Defines the input data which will be consumed by Process Engine

- **Output parameters:** Defines the output data which will be exposed to the user and/or the system

The individual fields for each parameter group are described in detail below.

### General task parameters
All Human Task types require general task parameters. These general parameters are described in [Workplace 2 Human Tasks](/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1).

![](data:image/png;base64,)Configuration window for general task parameters in Process Designer

### Input parameters
In addition to the [basic input parameters](/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1#basic-input-parameters) common to all Human Task types, the Composer Human Task also requires the following type-specific input parameters:

Field

Type

Mandatory or optional

Values

Description

`composerUrl`

text/plain

Mandatory

Exactly 1

URL of the Composer to be embedded

`templateNames`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

Relative path to ITX templates within Content Repository

`templateLabels`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

List of template names/labels, where the order should match the order in templateNames

`inputXml`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

XMLs for resolving dynamic data in the template

`inputXmlNames`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

List of XML data names as they are referenced in the template.

`idxDocumentNames`

text/plain

Optional

0..1

Composer document in IDX format

`refreshProcess`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

Optional path to a process definition which will be executed when the XML input data is refreshed in Composer.

### Output parameters
In addition to the [basic output parameters](/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1#basic-output-parameters) common to all Human Task types, the Composer Human Task also requires the following type-specific output parameters:

Field

Type

Values

Description

`idxDocuments`

text/plain

Exactly 1

Composer document in IDX format

`xmlOutputData`

text/plain

0..1

XML that contains the user inputs and building blocks inside insertion points, including building block parameters and rendered content

Composer is a web-based application for editing document templates which were created with Business Designer. It is used mainly to resolve dynamic fields into real data read from a database.

Process Designer is a GUI tool for creating and testing Infinica Process Definitions (IPD). It&#39;s a support tool for Process Engine, providing a graphical editing and log interface and removing the necessity to manually write XML processes in a text editor.
